This example creates a basic stylized scrollbar:

```css  
/* Scrollbar Styling Example */

/* The style below will be applied to all elements with overflow-y set to auto/scroll or visible.

```css

/* General Styles for the Page */

body {
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  margin: 20px;
  height: 200vh; /* Forcing a long page to demonstrate scrolling */
}

/* Styles for Custom Scrollbar */

::-webkit-scrollbar {
  width: 10px;
  height: 10px;
  border-radius: 0px;
}

::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb {
  background-color: #66CCCC; /* Blue-ish color for the thumb */
  border-radius: 50px;
  box-shadow: inset 6px 0 9px rgba(255, 255, 255,.3);
}

::-webkit-scrollbar-track-piece {
  background-color: #F2F2F7;
  -webkit-border-radius: 10px;
}

/* Optional hover effect */

::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb:hover {
  background-color: #003399; /* Darker blue on hover */
}
```

