 Here's an example:

```css

/* For Chrome, Safari and Opera */
.example {
  overflow-y: auto;
}

.example::-webkit-scrollbar {
    width: 10px; /* width of the entire scrollbar */
}

.example::-webkit-scrollbar-track {
    background-color: #F0F0F0; /* color of the tracking area */
}

.example::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb {
    background-color: #666; /* color of the thumb, the part you click and drag */
}

.example::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb:hover {
    background-color: #555; /* color of the thumb when hovered upon */
}

.example::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb:active {
    background-color: #333; /* color of the thumb when clicked upon */
}

/* For Firefox */
.example {
  scrollbar-width: thin;
}

.example scrollbar-color: #666 transparent;

```

To use this code, first ensure your element has `overflow` set to something other than `visible` in its CSS definition.
